quran[45]{c,v,t}:
  50,1,"Qaf. By the Glorious Qur'aan, [We swear its authenticity]"
  50,2,"But they wonder that there has come to them a Warner [from Allah] from among themselves. So the suppressors of the Truth say, \"This is a strange thing"
  50,3,"What! When we die and have become dust, (shall we rise again to life?) That is a return far [from being ever possible]"
  50,4,We do know what the earth takes away from them. And with Us is a record protected
  50,5,But they deny the Truth when it comes to them. And so they are in a confused state of mind
  50,6,"Do they not look at the sky above them — how We have made it and adorned it, and see that there are no cracks in it"
  50,7,And We have spread out the earth and cast mountains into it. And We have caused every kind of beautiful spouse of herbage grow in it
  50,8,To be observed and commemorated by every devotee turning to Allah
  50,9,"And We send down from the sky rain as a blessing, and We produce therewith gardens and seed for the harvest"
  50,10,"And tall palm-trees, with shoots of fruit-stalks, piled one over another"
  50,11,"A provision for (Allah's) subjects. And We give life therewith [with rain] to land that is dead. Thus will the coming out of the dead from their graves [Resurrection] be"
  50,12,"[Resurrection] was denied before them by the People of Noah, the Companions of the Rass, and the Thamood"
  50,13,"And of AAad, of Pharaoh, the brethren of Lot"
  50,14,"The Companions of the Wood, and the People of Tubba' (an ancient tribe) — all of them rejected the Messengers, and My warning (to them) was duly fulfilled"
  50,15,Were We then weary with the first Creation that they should be in such a confused state of mind about a new Creation
  50,16,"And We did create man, and We know the promptings of his own self. And We are closer to him than any bodily channel having access into his brain"
  50,17,"When the two frequently confronting voices, one located on the right and one on the left, confront each other"
  50,18,"He utters not a word but is there a sentinel by him, ready [to record it]"
  50,19,"And the pangs of death will bring the Truth home to him. \"This was the thing you kept away from"
  50,20,And then the Trumpet is blown — there then is the Day promised
  50,21,And every soul comes forth accompanied by a driver and a witness
  50,22,"You were careless about this. Now that We have taken off your cover from you, strong is your eyesight this Day"
  50,23,"And his Companion [witness] says, \"It's ready here — what in my hand is [man's record]"
  50,24,"Throw into Hell every stubborn suppressor of evidence proving existence of Allah [with attributes as given in the Qur'aan]"
  50,25,"Who was forbidding what was good, transgressing all bounds, and casting doubts and suspicions"
  50,26,Who had set up other god/s besides Allah! So throw him into the severe punishment
  50,27,"His Companion says, \"Our Lord! I did not make him transgress, but he was (himself) gone far astray"
  50,28,"He [Allah] says, \"Quarrel not in My Presence; and I did send you the warning in advance"
  50,29,"No alteration in the Word with Me, and I am never unjust to My subjects"
  50,30,"That Day We ask Hell, \"Are you full?\" And it asks, \"Are there any more"
  50,31,"And the Garden [of Paradise] is brought near for the pious and righteous, and it is no longer a distant objective [for them]"
  50,32,"This is what you were promised. [And this is what was promised] to every one who turned (to Allah in sincere repentance) and protected (himself against satanic influence)"
  50,33,"Who feared the Gracious One without physically seeing Him with worldly eyes, and has come with a mind turned in devotion (to Him)"
  50,34,"Enter therein [in Paradise] in Peace and Security; this is time of eternal life"
  50,35,"There is for them therein all that they desire. And [there is besides] much more with Us"
  50,36,"And how many a generation before them, stronger in power than they, did We destroy! They had wandered through the lands in search of a place of escape"
  50,37,Certainly indeed in this is a lesson to learn for any who has an understanding mind or who lends an insightful ear
  50,38,We created the heavens and the earth and all things in between in six periods of time. And weariness did not even touch Us
  50,39,"Have patience, then, over what they say, and glorify your Lord with praise, before the rising of the sun and before its setting"
  50,40,"And glorify Him during parts of the night, and post prostrations"
  50,41,"And listen the Day when the Caller calls out from a place quite near, —"
  50,42,The Day when they hear a real mighty Blast — that is the Day of Resurrection
  50,43,It is indeed We Who give life and cause death; and to Us is the final destination
  50,44,That Day the earth swiftly separates from them. That gathering — it is easy for Us
  50,45,We know what they say! And you are not to be coercive on them. So admonish with the Qur'an such as fear My Warning